{"title_page": "Laura Dean (actress)", "text_new": "'''Laura Dean''' (born '''Laura Francine Deutscher'''; May 27, 1963) is an American film and television actress and voice actress who is known for the roles of Sophie in the 3rd and 4th seasons of ''[[Friends (TV series)|Friends]]''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.broadwaybox.com/daily-scoop/fame-friends-alum-laura-dean-has-your-intro-to-opera/|title=Fame & Friends Alum Laura Dean Has Your Intro to Great Opera|website=BroadwayBox.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://54below.com/events/laura-dean/|title=Laura Dean|website=Feinstein's/54 Below|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>, of a lead character Tamara in ''[[Princess Gwenevere and the Jewel Riders]]'',<ref name=ibdb>[https://www.ibb.com/broadway-cast-staff/laura-dean-82258 ]{{dead link|date=February 2020}}</ref> and on ''Christmas in Cartoontown''. Since she was 10 years old, she also played the [[New York City Opera]] for five years in ''[[La boh\u00e8me]]'', ''[[Die tote Stadt]]'' and ''[[Mefistofele]]''. She is best known as the character \"Lisa\" the ballet dancer who gets kicked out of the dance department in the film ''[[Fame (1980 film)|Fame]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/picks-and-pans-review-fame-then-and-now-vol-59-no-23/|title=Picks and Pans Review: Fame Then and Now|website=PEOPLE.com|language=EN|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> She also appeared in the Broadway musical version of ''[[Doonesbury]]'' and as the mother of the title character in ''[[The Who's Tommy]]''.<ref name=ibdb/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-production/doonesbury-4240|title=Doonesbury \u2013 Broadway Musical \u2013 Original &#124; IBDB}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|0212847|Laura Dean}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dean, Laura}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{US-screen-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP IMDb refimprove|only=yes|date=April 2012}} \n'''Laura Dean''' (born '''Laura Francine Deutscher'''; May 27, 1963) is an American film and television actress and voice actress who is known for the roles of Sophie in the 3rd and 4th seasons of ''[[Friends (TV series)|Friends]]'', of a lead character Tamara in ''[[Princess Gwenevere and the Jewel Riders]]'',<ref name=ibdb>[https://www.ibb.com/broadway-cast-staff/laura-dean-82258 ]{{dead link|date=February 2020}}</ref> and on ''Christmas in Cartoontown''. Since she was 10 years old, she also played the [[New York City Opera]] for five years in ''[[La boh\u00e8me]]'', ''[[Die tote Stadt]]'' and ''[[Mefistofele]]''. She is best known as the character \"Lisa\" the ballet dancer who gets kicked out of the dance department in the film ''[[Fame (1980 film)|Fame]]''. She also appeared in the Broadway musical version of ''[[Doonesbury]]'' and as the mother of the title character in ''[[The Who's Tommy]]''.<ref name=ibdb/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-production/doonesbury-4240|title=Doonesbury \u2013 Broadway Musical \u2013 Original &#124; IBDB}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|0212847|Laura Dean}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dean, Laura}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{US-screen-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Cardiffbear88", "label": "safe", "comment": "Sources", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laura_Dean_(actress)"}
{"title_page": "Padalarang railway station", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=November 2011}}\n{{Infobox station\n | name          = Padalarang Station\n | image         = COLLECTIE TROPENMUSEUM Het spoorwegstation van Padalarang in aanbouw TMnr 60052211.jpg\n | image_caption = The Padalarang railway station under construction (1890-1910)\n | address       = [[Padalarang, West Bandung|Padalarang]], [[West Bandung Regency]], [[West Java]]\n | country       = [[Indonesia]]\n | line          = {{ubl|[[Cikampek\u2013Padalarang railway|Cikampek\u2013Padalarang]]\n[[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|Manggarai\u2013Padalarang]]\n[[Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan railway|Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan]]}}\n | other         =\n | platform      =\n | tracks        = 5\n | parking       = Available\n | bicycle       =\n | baggage_check =\n | passengers    =\n | pass_year     =\n | pass_percent  =\n | pass_system   =\n | opened        =\n | rebuilt       =\n | ADA           = Available\n | code          = PDL\n | owned         = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | operator      = Indonesian Railway Company<br>[[Kereta Api Logistik]]\n | zone          =\n | services      = Patas Bandung Raya<br>Lokal Bandung Raya<br>Lokal Cibatu<br>Lokal Simandra\n | mpassengers   =\n | coordinates   = {{coord|6|50|34.89|S|107|29|50.38|E|type:landmark}}\n | elevation     = +695 M\n | native_name   = ''{{smaller|Stasiun Padalarang}}''\n}}\n'''Padalarang Station''' is a train station in [[West Bandung Regency]], [[West Java]].\n\nThe station is located near the Cihaliwung area and Cihaliwung traditional market, on the heart of the capital city of Western Bandung Regency, the [[Padalarang, West Bandung|Padalarang]] town.\n\nThe station located on the western side of Bandung Cities, it is the point where 2 railways route (Jakarta - Cikampek - Padalarang) and (Jakarta - Bogor - Sukabumi - Padalarang) merged.\n\n==Destination==\nThe train station serves several economy class train both to the west side or to the east side, and also serves number of commuter train.\n\nTrains that are accessed from this station :\n* '''Serayu''' to [[Purwokerto Station|Purwokerto]] and [[Pasar Senen Station|Pasar Senen]]\n* '''Argo Parahyangan''' to [[Gambir Station|Gambir]] and [[Bandung Station|Bandung]]\nCommuter trains :\n* '''KA Simandra''' to [[Purwakarta Station|Purwakarta]] and [[Cibatu Station|Cibatu]]\n* '''Lokal Bandung Raya''' to [[Cicalengka Station|Cicalengka]]\n\n==Bandung Urban Railway==\nTo ease traffic congestion at the Greater Bandung roads, the Central government will make Bandung Urban Railway which use electric trains with double tracks line between Padalarang-Cicalengka through Bandung. In November 2011, mapping of Padalarang-Bandung route and feasibility study of Bandung-Cicalengka route have been done by local government.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pikiran-rakyat.com/node/166736 |title=Padalarang-Bandung-Cicalengka Bakal Dilayani Kereta |date=November 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Padalarang Station}}\n*{{in lang|id}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20090508004457/http://www.kereta-api.com/ PT KAI] - the Indonesian rail company\n*{{in lang|id}} [http://www.semboyan35.com/ Forum Semboyan35] - Indonesian Rail fans Forum\n*{{in lang|id}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20130113033843/http://stasiunbandung.com/stasiun-padalarang/ Padalarang Train Station]\n\n{{coord|6|50|34.89|S|107|29|50.38|E|type:landmark|display=title}}\n{{S-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Cilame}}\n|route    = [[Cikampek\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Cikampek\u2013Padalarang</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|rows2    = 2\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Cikampek}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Tagogapu}}\n|route    = [[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Manggarai\u2013Padalarang</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|hide2    = true\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Manggarai}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Gadobangkong}}\n|col      = FF0000\n|term2    = {{stnlnk|Kasugihan}}\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|West Java}}\n\n[[category:West Bandung Regency]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in West Java]]\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{more footnotes|date=November 2011}}\n{{Infobox station\n | name          = Padalarang Station\n | image         = COLLECTIE TROPENMUSEUM Het spoorwegstation van Padalarang in aanbouw TMnr 60052211.jpg\n | image_caption = The Padalarang railway station under construction (1890-1910)\n | address       = [[Padalarang, West Bandung|Padalarang]], [[West Bandung Regency]], [[West Java]]\n | country       = [[Indonesia]]\n | line          = {{ubl|[[Cikampek\u2013Padalarang railway|Cikampek\u2013Padalarang]]\n[[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|Manggarai\u2013Padalarang]]\n[[Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan railway|Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan]]}}\n | other         =\n | platform      =\n | tracks        = 5\n | parking       = Available\n | bicycle       =\n | baggage_check =\n | passengers    =\n | pass_year     =\n | pass_percent  =\n | pass_system   =\n | opened        =\n | rebuilt       =\n | ADA           = Available\n | code          = PDL\n | owned         = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | operator      = Indonesian Railway Company<br>[[Kereta Api Logistik]]\n | zone          =\n | services      = Patas Bandung Raya<br>Lokal Bandung Raya<br>Lokal Cibatu<br>Lokal Simandra\n | mpassengers   =\n | coordinates   = {{coord|6|50|34.89|S|107|29|50.38|E|type:landmark}}\n | elevation     = +695 M\n | native_name   = ''{{smaller|Stasiun Padalarang}}''\n}}\n'''Padalarang Station''' is a train station in [[West Bandung Regency]], [[West Java]].\n\nThe station is located near the Cihaliwung area and Cihaliwung traditional market, on the heart of the capital city of Western Bandung Regency, the [[Padalarang, West Bandung|Padalarang]] town.\n\nThe station located on the western side of Bandung Cities, it is the point where 2 railways route (Jakarta - Cikampek - Padalarang) and (Jakarta - Bogor - Sukabumi - Padalarang) merged.\n\n==Destination==\nThe train station serves several economy class train both to the west side or to the east side, and also serves number of commuter train.\n\nTrains that are accessed from this station :\n* '''Serayu''' to [[Purwokerto Station|Purwokerto]] and [[Pasar Senen Station|Pasar Senen]]\n* '''Argo Parahyangan''' to [[Gambir Station|Gambir]] and [[Bandung Station|Bandung]]\nCommuter trains :\n* '''KA Simandra''' to [[Purwakarta Station|Purwakarta]] and [[Cibatu Station|Cibatu]]\n* '''Lokal Bandung Raya''' to [[Cicalengka Station|Cicalengka]]\n\n==Bandung Urban Railway==\nTo ease traffic congestion at the Greater Bandung roads, the Central government will make Bandung Urban Railway which use electric trains with double tracks line between Padalarang-Cicalengka through Bandung. In November 2011, mapping of Padalarang-Bandung route and feasibility study of Bandung-Cicalengka route have been done by local government.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pikiran-rakyat.com/node/166736 |title=Padalarang-Bandung-Cicalengka Bakal Dilayani Kereta |date=November 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Padalarang Station}}\n*{{in lang|id}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20090508004457/http://www.kereta-api.com/ PT KAI] - the Indonesian rail company\n*{{in lang|id}} [http://www.semboyan35.com/ Forum Semboyan35] - Indonesian Rail fans Forum\n*{{in lang|id}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20130113033843/http://stasiunbandung.com/stasiun-padalarang/ Padalarang Train Station]\n\n{{coord|6|50|34.89|S|107|29|50.38|E|type:landmark|display=title}}\n{{S-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Cilame}}\n|route    = [[Cikampek\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Cikampek\u2013Padalarang</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|rows2    = 2\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Cikampek}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Tagogapu}}\n|route    = [[Manggarai\u2013Padalarang railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Manggarai\u2013Padalarang</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|hide2    = true\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Manggarai}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Padalarang\u2013Kasugihan</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Gadobangkong}}\n|col      = FF0000\n|term2    = {{stnlnk|Kasugihan}}\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|West Java}}\n\n[[category:West Bandung Regency]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in West Java]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in West Java]]\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Buildings and structures in West JavausingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padalarang_railway_station"}
